  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5656",
  "title": "NextJS - `createURL` should run server side",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\n`createURL` returns an empty URL on the server and only populates on the client.\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Go the sandbox\r\n2. Disable Javascript\r\n3. Observe that the links are empty\r\n<img width=\"376\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2023-05-31 at 12 09 06 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/10588097/3bcd0dbd-9231-4874-8cfa-7fcc66c52b61\">\r\n\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/refinement-list-sort-issue-forked-i8kn3o?file=%2Fcomponents%2FRefinementList.js%3A9%2C11\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nExpect that the links are populated server side. Theoretically this should be possible since we are running `getServerState` on the server and know the UI state prior to SSR. (See https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5236#issuecomment-1566414241).\n\n### Package version\n\nalgoliasearch 4.17.1, react-instantsearch-hooks-web 6.44.0\n\n### Operating system\n\nMac 11.6.5\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome 113.0.5672.126\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
